author: wcax.com
title: Gas prices fall 3 cents in New Hampshire in last week
text:
CONCORD, N.H. (AP) - Gas prices in New Hampshire have fallen 3 cents per gallon in the past week, to an average of $2.65.
Gasbuddy.com, which surveyed 875 gas stations in the state, says that's 8 cents less than the national average, which also fell 3 cents to $2.73.
Gas prices in New Hampshire are 93.6 cents lower per gallon than a year ago and 8 cents lower per gallon than a month ago.
The national average is 79.1 cents less per gallon than a year ago and fell 5.2 cents per gallon in the past month.
